inheritance :
inheritance is fundamentals concept that allows a class to inherit the properties and behavior of another class

types
single inheritance
multilevel inheritance
Hierarchical inheritance

// single inheritance
when a class extend another class then this is called single inheritance
when a derived class or subclass inherits from only one base class or super class then it is called single inheritance

syntax
class subClass extends superClass{

}

this and super keyword in java
this keyword : this keyword is a reference variable that refers to the current object. it can be used to refer the current instance of the class in which it appears . the "this" keyword is particularly useful when there is a need to disambiguate instance variables from local variables or parameters with same name

super keyword : super keyword is used to refer to the immediate parent class object . it is commonly used in the context of inheritance to access members of the super class

multilevel Inheritance
When a class extends to another class that also extends some other class then this is called multilevel inheritance

multilevel inheritance refers ti a situation where a class extends another class, and then another class extends the derived class

Hierarchical Inheritance
When a class is extended by two or more classes then it is called hierarchical inheritance

